Hungary Confirms Ending Most Industry Taxes After 2012, MTI Says

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-10-18T13:25:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/hungary-confirms-ending-most-industry-taxes-after-2012-mti-says.html
Hungary will no longer levy
extraordinary taxes on the energy, retail and telecommunications
industries after 2012 while halving a similar tax on the
financial industry, MTI reported, citing Peter Beno Banai, an
assistant state secretary at the  Economy Ministry .   Revenue from the financial industry tax is forecast to drop
to 90 billion forint from 2013, from 187 billion forint in 2012,
Banai told lawmakers today in Budapest, according to the state-
run news service.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Zoltan Simon at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net  